content:
Thank you for providing the documentation. I can see that the `convert` command from ImageMagick is available for image processing. To convert an image to grayscale, I can use the `-colorspace Gray` option.

Let me convert all the extracted keyframes to grayscale.

```json
{
  "analysis": "The image_editing skill uses ImageMagick's `convert` command. To convert images to grayscale, I can use the `-colorspace Gray` option. I'll convert all keyframes_*.png files to grayscale in-place.",
  "plan": "Use the `convert` command with the `-colorspace Gray` option to convert each keyframe PNG file to grayscale. I'll modify the files in-place by overwriting the originals.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "for file in /root/keyframes_*.png; do convert \"$file\" -colorspace Gray \"$file\"; done\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    }
  ]
}
```
